    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1954-06-03T09:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1954-06-03T09:00:00-05:00" n="663"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d663">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">751G.00/6–354: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">United States Delegation</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Department of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">top secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Geneva</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1954-06-03T15:00:00+01:00"
                            >June 3, 1954—3 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_Dulte1">Dulte</gloss> 142. Repeated information Paris 376.
                    Paris limit distribution. I told <persName corresp="#p_EA1">Eden</persName> this
                    morning that with the deteriorating military situation Indochina and the
                    Vietnam-French military talks now going on here I was seriously concerned that
                    if within the next week or two the Communists offered France a cease-fire the
                    French would be in a weak position to resist and might have to accept without
                    any agreement on effective international control machinery or with machinery
                    which would be purely nominal. <persName corresp="#p_EA1">Eden</persName> said
                    he fully shared my fears in this regard.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_SWB1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Smith</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
